DON’T FORGET about our additional meal (breakfast and lunch) distribution on Tuesdays and Thursdays!

Students (or their parents) can pick up three days of frozen lunches to conveniently re-heat at home. Pick up meals at Flowing Wells Junior High from 3:30pm - 5:30pm. The cost of meals will be based on the student’s free, reduced, or paid status with the district.

We hope to see you TOMORROW! The meals will cover Friday, Monday, and Tuesday lunches and breakfasts.

post_text:
We asked our seniors to share their best advice for the younger students in our district, read their responses below:

✨ Keep reaching for the stars and don't let anything stop you from what you want to achieve.
✨Make sure to have fun while working at school.
✨Always try your best because it always shows.
✨ It's never too soon to start thinking about college and getting good grades!
✨ Keep going no matter how hard it gets.
✨ Dream big. Study hard. If you have a dream, go achieve it.
✨ Always do your homework.

Great advice, don't you think? Thank you, Class of 2020!!

💙💛

post_text: Congratulations to Mr. Dax Valles, who was approved by the FW Governing Board to be the new principal at Homer Davis Elementary! Dax graduated from Flowing Wells High School, taught at FWHS, became an assistant principal at Flowing Wells Junior High, and then principal at Sentinel Peak High School. Mr. Valles is extremely excited to join the Dragon family!💜💙

Desayuno: 7:30 - 8:30 AM
Almuerzo: 12:00 - 1:00 PM

- Cualquier estudiante de 18 años ó menos puede recoger un desayuno y almuerzo para llevar.
- La comida sera gratis para cualquier persona menor de 18 años, independientemente de inscripción ó estatus de comida gratis/reducida.

𝗗𝗜𝗗 𝗬𝗢𝗨 𝗛𝗘𝗔𝗥?

The Flowing Wells JROTC Rifle Team qualified for the National JROTC Championship at Camp Perry. Teams from all 50 states, the Pacific, and Europe participated. Each service (Army, Navy, Air Force and Marine Corps) can only send seven teams to National, for the Army JROTC there were 𝒐𝒗𝒆𝒓 1600 𝒕𝒆𝒂𝒎𝒔 and Flowing Wells was number seven!

𝗖𝗼𝗻𝗴𝗿𝗮𝘁𝘂𝗹𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝘀:
Casey Downing
Kaitlyn Rendon
Kaitlyn Martin (Ironwood Ridge HS)
Israel Martinez- Team Captain
Tristan Konigsfeld
Coach: Vincent Tolliver

Way to go, Cabs!!

ATTENTION: FUTURE JUNIOR HIGH MUSTANG PARENTS & STUDENTS!

Have a future 7th grader or just want to learn more about what Flowing Wells Junior High has to offer? Join us on Tuesday, February 4th from 6:00-7:00 p.m. in the Flowing Wells Junior High Auditorium to get a glimpse of life as a Mustang.

Come and learn about the outstanding education your child will receive at Flowing Wells Junior High, including all the exciting opportunities beyond the classroom. Staff and administrators will share information and answer all of your questions.

By attending, you will have the opportunity to win:

✦ FWJH Apparel
✦ Fee Waivers (Classes and P.E. uniforms)

Welcome, future Mustangs!

post_text:
“𝗜𝗻 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆 𝘄𝗮𝗹𝗸 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵 𝗻𝗮𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝗼𝗻𝗲 𝗿𝗲𝗰𝗲𝗶𝘃𝗲𝘀 𝗳𝗮𝗿 𝗺𝗼𝗿𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗮𝗻 𝗵𝗲 𝘀𝗲𝗲𝗸𝘀.”
– John Muir 🌵

For the past seven years, The Walter Douglas Hiking Club, in partnership with the Saguaro National Park, has invited students to get outdoors! The club provides members with several outdoor experiences and culminates in an overnight camp out on Mt. Lemmon in the spring. Members are also encouraged to continue their involvement with the park through volunteer opportunities in the Cactus Ranger program, which can eventually lead to post high school internships. Currently, four FW students from The Walter Douglas Hiking Club have gone on to participate in the Cactus Ranger program!

Thank you to the Saguaro National Park, and club advisors Mrs. Camero and Ms. Sisson, for providing students these amazing opportunities!
